    <li>CT Procedure Screening Questionnaire</li>
    <li>Protocol for Management of Patients with Iodine Allergy or Known Allergy to CT IV Radiographic Contrast Media</li>
    <li>Protocol for Management of Patients Taking Metformin Scheduled for CT Studies with IV Radiographic Contrast Media</li>
</ul>
<h3>
Additional Applicable Instructions</h3>
<ul>
    <li>CT Abdominal-Pelvis IV and Oral Preparation:</li>
    	<ul>
        <li>Patient must arrive 1 hour prior to the scheduled exam.</li>
        <li>Avoid food or drink 3 hours before the scheduled exam.</li>
		</ul>
    <li>CT Angio Cardiac Preparation:</li>
    <ul>
        <li>Avoid Caffeine, 4 hours prior to the scheduled exam time.</li>
        <li>Avoid food or drink 3 hours before the scheduled exam time.</li>
        <li>Patient must arrive 30 minutes prior to the scheduled exam.</li>
        </ul>
    <li>CT Virtual Colonography Preparation:</li>
    <ul>
        <li>A prep kit will be mailed to patients 3 days prior to the scheduled exam date</li>
        <li>Patient must arrive 1 hour prior to the scheduled exam time to allow adequate time for processing and preparation purposes.</li>
        </ul>
    <li>CT Perfusion Study with Diamox Preparation:</li>
    <ul>
        <li>Avoid food or drink 3 hours before the scheduled exam time.</li>
        <li>Patient must arrive 30 minutes prior to the scheduled exam time to allow adequate time for processing and preparation purposes.</li>
        </ul>
    <li>CT Radiation Treatment Planning:</li>
    <ul>
        <li>Patient must be accompanied by a radiation treatment therapist.</li>
        <li>Patient must arrive 30 minutes prior to the scheduled exam time to allow adequate time for processing and preparation purposes.</li> 
